name: Gift voucher - Carte cadeau
description:
A Gift Voucher makes for the perfect gift for any Sen No Sen fan. Gift vouchers are available in values of €25, €50, €100, €150, €200, €250 & €300 and redeemable online at http://store.sennosen.com or in any Sen No Sen flagship stores. 

We send the gift card with a code in order the recipient can order online.

- The recipient will not be emailed, the email is for keeping track of the credit. You can choose to receive the gift card to offer it or we can send it to recipient.
- Valid in-store and online
- Physical copy sent to buyer or to recipient (please, note where you want we send the card)


Le chèque cadeau est le meilleur moyen de faire plaisir à vos amis qui aiment Sen No Sen, sans se tromper dans le choix du cadeau.
Il y a plusieurs montants au choix: €30, €50, €100, €150, €200, €250 et €300.

La carte cadeau vous est envoyée si vous souhaitez la remettre en main propre à la personne pour Noël.
Nous pouvons envoyer la carte cadeau directement à la personne concernée, dans ce cas, n'oubliez pas de nous indiquer l'adresse de livraison.

Le bénéficiaire peut ensuite se rendre dans une de nos boutiques avec la carte ou commander sur le site avec le code qui sera indiqué sur la carte.

name: SEN NO SEN "lifeguard" hoodie sweater
description:
This season, we've redesigned the "hoodie sweater" that will never go out of fashion.
We've mixed some details to bring the classic round neck sweater style. Kangaroo pockets are now inside the sweater and we've added stitches details like a round neck piece. 
At least, leather pieces and cord give it the urban style 
"lifeguard" print is inspired by famous Hawaiian lifeguard logo.

- 100% cotton 
- leather patchs
- made in Europe


Pour cette saison, nous avons revisité l'indémodable sweat capuche.
Afin de lui donner plus de style qu'un simple accessoire de sportswear, nous avons tout d'abord retravaillé les détails du col et retiré poche kangourou (les poches sont à l'intérieur) pour lui donner un look de sweat col ron classique, plus tendance actuellement. 
Les empiècements en cuir et le cordon qui rappelle une corde marine lui donne un style plus urbain.
Enfin le print est une variante du fameux logo des sauveteurs à Hawaii.

- 100% cotton 
- empiècements cuir
- fabriqué en Europe

name: SEN NO SEN "back from the Ocean" T-shirt
description:
We've asked to Steven Burke to design a logo for us and this model is born from our collaboration. We love this simple and nice handwriting inspired from a true piece of wood found at a sailor house.

- Designed by Steven Burke (www.luckylefthand.com)
- 100% cotton
- Made in Europe



On a demandé à Steven Burke de nous dessiné un logo et ce modèle est le né de notre collaboration. On adore le rendu à la fois simple et authentique de cette phrase couchée à la base sur un morceau de bois trouvé chez un marin-pêcheur.

- Dessiné par Steven Burke (www.luckylefthand.com)
- 100% coton
- Fabriqué en Europe

The Surfer's Journal 21.6 (current issue)
description: Heaped with surf kink, the latest issue of TSJ is anything but normal. Daniel Thomson’s midnight speed run at Lennox gets things started. Once Tom Curren cops to MR at Sunset as the best surfer he’s ever seen, you’ll find Mark Cunningham surfing (yes, standing) among a mob of rarely seen surf subjects. If this dose of the offbeat has you re-evaluating your equipment, consider the virtues of sail-power with Greenough and our case for turning up the volume.

name: The Surfer's Journal 21.4
description: Featuring Thomas Campbell’s gritty Dave Rastovich composition on the cover, issue 21.4 opens with Ken “Skindog” Collins telling of why, after only a handful of sessions at Maverick’s, Shane Dorian is the best surfer he’s ever seen. Jeff Johnson delves into the handiwork of Hawaiian craftsman Jon Pyzel, and again we Spin The Globe. On the flip side, look for a never-before-surfed Canadian slab to kick off Undercurrents, while the point of pointy nosed boards get scrutinized and the Midwest waverider gets his due.

name: DVD - Trash by Todd Barnes
description:
le nouveau film de Todd Barnes, TRASH vient clore la trilogie (THRASH puis TRASH'D). Pour les amoureux des belles images, un film soigné, super montage et des images incroyables. A posséder dans sa vidéothèque.

From the Maker of Video, Thrash & Thrash'd Todd Barnes delivers the goods again. Probably the most highly anticipated bodyboard Flick oif the Year Trash doesn't dissapoint.

Found Boards in association with Leboogie Magazine & Bodyboard King proudly present TRASH / A boog flick with creative madness!

The opening sequence features the voice of GOD... Mike Stewart as he discuss his thoughts on the present earth, the exponential growth of the human race and all the garbage and negativity that comes with that. This accommpanied with some mind bending visuals sums up our society these dayz, industrial, commerical, corporate, hollywood overload!

Our only escape from this world of TRASH... just go Boog'n

The next 45 minutes amplifies high-tech, explosive Bodyboarding cut and chopped to underground sounds you ain't heard. Watch Nuggen from a Heli, The North Shore of Oahu pulse, Mitch Rawlins break the sound barrier, Mexican perfection, Thomas Robinson Styln', Chris James finds KONY and Brendan Newton goes Bananas in Van Diemans Land. Along with the rest of the worlds best bodyboarders tearing apart Samoa, Western Australia, East Coast Oz, Chile, Puerto Rico and the Canary Islands.
